title: Earthquake of magnitude 7.6 hits Caribbean, triggers tsunami warning
description: A powerful magnitude 7.6 earthquake hit the Caribbean Sea near the Cayman Islands, prompting tsunami warnings. The quake struck 125 miles south-southwest of George Town. Authorities are closely monitoring the situation with advisories issued for Puerto Rico and the Virgin Islands. No immediate damage or casualties have been reported, and coastal residents are urged to stay alert.
